{"parse":{"title":"Carolyn Muessig","pageid":48339666,"revid":859811987,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>Carolyn Anne Muessig</b> is Professor of Medieval Religion at the <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Bristol\" title=\"University of Bristol\">University of Bristol</a>. A graduate of <a href=\"/wiki/Fulton-Montgomery_Community_College\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Fulton-Montgomery Community College\">Fulton-Montgomery Community College</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/State_University_of_New_York_at_Buffalo\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"State University of New York at Buffalo\">State University of New York at Buffalo</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/University_of_Toronto\" title=\"University of Toronto\">University of Toronto</a>, the <a href=\"/wiki/Pontifical_Institute_of_Mediaeval_Studies\" title=\"Pontifical Institute of Mediaeval Studies\">Pontifical Institute of Mediaeval Studies</a>, and the <a href=\"/wiki/Universit%C3%A9_de_Montr%C3%A9al\" title=\"Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al\">Universit\u00e9 de Montr\u00e9al</a>, Muessig is a specialist in the history of medieval preaching, <a href=\"/wiki/Jacques_de_Vitry\" title=\"Jacques de Vitry\">Jacques de Vitry</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Francis_of_Assisi\" title=\"Francis of Assisi\">Francis of Assisi</a>, <a href=\"/wiki/Catherine_of_Siena\" title=\"Catherine of Siena\">Catherine of Siena</a> and female educators of the Middle Ages. She was co-editor (with <a href=\"/wiki/Veronica_O%27Mara\" title=\"Veronica O&#39;Mara\">Veronica O'Mara</a>) of <i>Medieval Sermon Studies</i> for 17 years and since 2001 she has been series co-editor with George Ferzoco of <i><a href=\"/wiki/Routledge_Studies_in_Medieval_Religion_and_Culture\" title=\"Routledge Studies in Medieval Religion and Culture\">Routledge Studies in Medieval Religion and Culture</a></i>.<sup id=\"cite_ref-1\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div id=\"toc\" class=\"toc\"><input type=\"checkbox\" role=\"button\" id=\"toctogglecheckbox\" class=\"toctogglecheckbox\" style=\"display:none\" /><div class=\"toctitle\" lang=\"en\" dir=\"ltr\"><h2>Contents</h2><span class=\"toctogglespan\"><label class=\"toctogglelabel\" for=\"toctogglecheckbox\"></label></span></div>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-1\"><a href=\"#Selected_publications\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Selected publications</span></a>\n<ul>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-2\"><a href=\"#Books_and_edited_volumes\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.1</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Books and edited volumes</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-2 tocsection-3\"><a href=\"#Articles_and_chapters\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">1.2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">Articles and chapters</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-4\"><a href=\"#External_links\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">2</span> <span class=\"toctext\">External links</span></a></li>\n<li class=\"toclevel-1 tocsection-5\"><a href=\"#References\"><span class=\"tocnumber\">3</span> <span class=\"toctext\">References</span></a></li>\n</ul>\n</div>\n\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Selected_publications\">Selected publications</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Carolyn_Muessig&amp;action=edit&amp;section=1\" title=\"Edit section: Selected publications\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Books_and_edited_volumes\">Books and edited volumes</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Carolyn_Muessig&amp;action=edit&amp;section=2\" title=\"Edit section: Books and edited volumes\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li><i>Medieval Monastic Preaching</i> (Leiden: Brill, 1998)</li>\n<li><i>The Faces of Women in the Sermons of Jacques de Vitry</i>. Toronto: Peregrina, 1999. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/092066959X\" title=\"Special:BookSources/092066959X\">092066959X</a>; <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780920669594\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780920669594\">9780920669594</a></li>\n<li><i>Preacher, Sermon and Audience in the Middle Ages</i> (Leiden: Brill, 2002)</li>\n<li><i>Medieval Monastic Education</i>, ed. with G. Ferzoco (New York; London: Continuum, 2005)</li>\n<li><i>Envisaging Heaven in the Middle Ages</i>. Co-edited with <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Ad_Putter&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Ad Putter (page does not exist)\">Ad Putter</a>. Routledge Studies in Medieval Religion and Culture, 6. London and New York: Routledge, 2007. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/0415383838\" title=\"Special:BookSources/0415383838\">0415383838</a> (hbk.); <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/020396621X\" title=\"Special:BookSources/020396621X\">020396621X</a> (ebk.); <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780415383837\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780415383837\">9780415383837</a>; <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9780203966211\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9780203966211\">9780203966211</a></li>\n<li><i>A Companion to Catherine of Siena</i>. Co-editor with <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=George_Ferzoco&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"George Ferzoco (page does not exist)\">George Ferzoco</a> and <a href=\"/wiki/Beverly_Mayne_Kienzle\" title=\"Beverly Mayne Kienzle\">Beverly Mayne Kienzle</a>. Brill's companions to the Christian tradition (ISSN 1871-6377) v. 32. Leiden and Boston: Brill, 2011. xvi, 395 p.&#160;: ill.&#160;; 25&#160;cm. <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9789004205550\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9789004205550\">9789004205550</a> (hardback&#160;: alk. paper); <a href=\"/wiki/International_Standard_Book_Number\" title=\"International Standard Book Number\">ISBN</a>&#160;<a href=\"/wiki/Special:BookSources/9004205551\" title=\"Special:BookSources/9004205551\">9004205551</a> (hardback&#160;: alk. paper)</li>\n<li><i>The Stigmata in Medieval and Early Modern Europe</i> (Oxford: Oxford University Press, 2018)</li></ul>\n<h3><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"Articles_and_chapters\">Articles and chapters</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Carolyn_Muessig&amp;action=edit&amp;section=3\" title=\"Edit section: Articles and chapters\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h3>\n<ul><li>'Can't Take My Eyes Off Of You': Mutual Gazing Between the Divine and Humanity in Late Medieval Preaching', <i>Optics, Ethics, and Art in the Thirteenth and Fourteenth Centuries</i>, ed. by H. Kessler and R. Newhauser (Toronto: Pontifical Institute of Mediaeval Studies) 17-28</li>\n<li>'Medieval Reportationes: Hearing and Listening to Sermons', <i>L\u2019Eloquence de la chair entre \u00e9criture et oralit\u00e9</i>, ed. by C. V. Meli and A. Heneveld (Paris: Honor\u00e9 Champion, 2018) 77-90</li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"External_links\">External links</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Carolyn_Muessig&amp;action=edit&amp;section=4\" title=\"Edit section: External links\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<ul><li>'A Perfect Miracle: The Stigmata in Pre-modern Europe', Professorial Inaugeral Lecture, University of Bristol, Wednesday 16 March 2016. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"http://www.bristol.ac.uk/pace/public-events/inaugural/2016/muessig.html/\">http://www.bristol.ac.uk/pace/public-events/inaugural/2016/muessig.html/</a></li>\n<li>'Performance and Female Preaching in Late Medieval and Early Modern Europe', Public lecture for the Oxford Medieval Studies Programme, Tuesday, June 12, 2018. <a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external free\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZEHJgcMXJpE\">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZEHJgcMXJpE</a></li></ul>\n<h2><span class=\"mw-headline\" id=\"References\">References</span><span class=\"mw-editsection\"><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">[</span><a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Carolyn_Muessig&amp;action=edit&amp;section=5\" title=\"Edit section: References\">edit</a><span class=\"mw-editsection-bracket\">]</span></span></h2>\n<div class=\"reflist\" style=\"list-style-type: decimal;\">\n<div class=\"mw-references-wrap\"><ol class=\"references\">\n<li id=\"cite_note-1\"><span class=\"mw-cite-backlink\"><b><a href=\"#cite_ref-1\">^</a></b></span> <span class=\"reference-text\"><a rel=\"nofollow\" class=\"external text\" href=\"http://research-information.bristol.ac.uk/en/persons/carolyn-a-muessig%28d6387739-f96b-4a87-8ed3-e1263e2bdc57%29.html\">Professor Carolyn Muessig.</a> University of Bristol. Retrieved 24 October 2015.</span>\n</li>\n</ol></div></div>\n<p><br />\n</p>\n<table class=\"metadata plainlinks stub\" role=\"presentation\" style=\"background:transparent\"><tbody><tr><td><a href=\"/wiki/File:Education_-_Grad_Hat.svg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"Stub icon\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/10/Education_-_Grad_Hat.svg/30px-Education_-_G